# .cursorrules — PowerPoint MCP Server Skills

You are assisting with `mcp-server-powerpoint`, a Windows-only MCP server that drives a live
PowerPoint desktop instance via COM. When using the PowerPoint MCP tools (not when editing this
repo's C# source), follow these rules:

## Session Rules

- Call `open_presentation(filePath)` before any editing tool; use the returned `sessionId` for
  every subsequent call.
- `create_presentation` creates a file on disk but does NOT open a session — always follow it
  with `open_presentation` before adding content.
- Call `save_presentation(sessionId)` before `close_presentation(sessionId)` to persist changes.
- `close_presentation` returns immediately; it does not wait for the PowerPoint process to fully
  exit. Do not poll for process exit.

## Indexing Rules

- `slideIndex`, `shapeIndex`, and table `row`/`column` are all **1-based**. The first slide is
  `slideIndex=1`, not `0`.

## Verification Rules

- After adding or repositioning any shape, table, chart, or image, call
  `export_slide_to_image(sessionId, slideIndex, outputPath)` and inspect the result before moving
  on or saving. Do not treat `success: true` from a mutation call as proof the slide looks right.
- For a finished multi-slide deck, call `export_all_slides_to_images` once as a final pass.

## Behavioral Rules

- Never ask the user clarifying questions you can answer yourself — use `list_sessions`,
  `get_slide_count`, `get_shape_count`, `get_text`, `get_layout`, `get_cell_text`,
  `get_chart_data`, `get_notes_text` to discover current state.
- Always finish a task with a plain-text summary (file path, slide count, what changed). Never
  end a turn with only a tool call.
- Prefer targeted updates (`set_cell_text`, `set_shape_position`, `set_shape_size`) over
  delete-and-recreate for small changes.
- `add_chart` supports exactly one data series per call — there is no multi-series parameter.
- There is no slide-reorder tool — plan the final slide order before calling `add_slide`.

## Full Reference

See `skills/shared/*.md` (also mirrored at `skills/powerpoint-mcp/references/*.md`) for complete
guidance: `behavioral-rules.md`, `workflows.md`, `deck-builder.md`, `slides-and-shapes.md`,
`text-formatting.md`, `tables.md`, `charts.md`, `images.md`, `speaker-notes.md`, `layouts.md`,
`export-and-verify.md`, `anti-patterns.md`.
